Level three water restrictions have been in effect since the beginning of the month as dam levels in the province remain critically low. CAPE TOWN The City of Cape Town has urged residents to further restrict water use as the metro is still falling short of its required savings target. Level three water restrictions have been in effect since the beginning of the month as dam levels in the province remain critically low in the wake of a gripping drought. The City s Ernest Sonnenberg says water saving tips are available on the metro's website. The City of Cape Town advises residents that overall water consumption since the implementation of level three water restriction is still 10% above the target of 800 million litres per day. WATCH: Avoid the fine: Tips on saving water(Edited by Masechaba Sefularo)